NORMALISED EXTRACT:
Module export forms and semantics (exact usable forms):
- Named export: export { name1, name2 as alias };
- Declaration export: export const name = value; export function fn() {} export class C {}
- Default export: export default expression; or export default function name() {} or export default class {}
- Re-export (from another module): export { name } from 'module'; export * from 'module'; export { default as alias } from 'module';
- Live binding semantics: exported bindings are live references to the original binding; updates to the exported variable in the source module are visible to importers.
- Static/top-level only: export statements must appear at top level of module code (not inside blocks or functions).

